    "created_at": "2015-08-03T06:34:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-03T06:34:55Z",
    "body": "C converts the integer constant 0 when used in a pointer context to the platform null pointer value. It seems like we'd need to do the same if we wanted to handle platforms with a non-zero null pointer, though that rule seems kind of insane and really error prone.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
